// Triết standard library — std.result
//
// `Result<T, E>` is the canonical type for "operation may fail with
// detail" per SPEC §2.5 (v0.4). Pair it with `T?` (nullable) for
// "value may be absent", and `Trilean` for "value has Unknown state":
//
//   T?                   — lookup, optional field, missing data.
//   Result<T, E>         — parse error, IO failure, capability denial.
//   Trilean              — Ł3 state with first-class Unknown.
//
// The Ok / Err variants intentionally mirror Rust's spelling so
// LLM-emitted code interoperates with mental models trained on the
// wider Rust ecosystem.

public enum Result<T, E> {
    Ok(T),
    Err(E),
}
